<%- include('partials/header', { title: 'About Indian Culture' }) %>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Your Website Title</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/global.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/culture.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <section class="cultural-highlights">
    <h2>Cultural Insights</h2>
    <div class="festival-list">
      <div class="festival">
        <h3>Diwali</h3>
        <img
          src="/images/diwali.jpeg.jpg"
          alt="Diwali"
          class="festival-image"
        />
        <p>Date: October 26, 2025</p>
        
        <p>
          Significance: Known as the Festival of Lights, Diwali symbolizes the
          victory of light over darkness and good over evil. It is celebrated
          with fireworks, sweets, and the lighting of lamps.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="festival">
        <h3>Holi</h3>
        <img src="/images/holi.jpg" alt="Holi" class="festival-image" />
        <p>Date: March 17, 2025</p>
        
        <p>
          Significance: Holi, the Festival of Colors, marks the arrival of
          spring. It is celebrated by throwing colored powders, singing, and
          dancing, symbolizing love and the triumph of good over evil.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="festival">
        <h3>Eid al-Fitr</h3>
        <img
          src="/images/eid-2024.jpg"
          alt="Eid al-Fitr"
          class="festival-image"
        />
        <p>Date: April 9, 2025</p>
       
        <p>
          Significance: Eid al-Fitr marks the end of Ramadan, the Islamic holy
          month of fasting. It is celebrated with prayers, feasting, and giving
          to charity.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="festival">
        <h3>Navratri</h3>
        <img
          src="/images/navaratri.jpeg.jpg"
          alt="Navratri"
          class="festival-image"
        />
        <p>Date: October 1, 2025</p>
        
        <p>
          Significance: Navratri is a nine-night festival dedicated to the
          worship of the goddess Durga. It includes fasting, dancing, and
          cultural performances.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="festival">
        <h3>Thrissur Pooram</h3>
        <img
          src="/images/thrissur pooram.jpg"
          alt="Thrissur Pooram"
          class="festival-image"
        />
        <p>Date: May 4, 2025</p>
        
        <p>
          Significance: Thrissur Pooram is one of the most famous and grand
          festivals in Kerala, celebrated in honor of Lord Shiva. The festival
          is known for its spectacular procession of elaborately decorated
          elephants, traditional percussion music, and vibrant fireworks.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    function logFestivalDate(elementId, festival) {
      const currentDate = new Date().toLocaleDateString();
      document.getElementById(elementId).textContent = currentDate; // Update the date in the <span>
      console.log(`${festival} Date: ${currentDate}`);
    }
  </script>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
